flowRoot.flowPara: 3A - ARC vs. URCR - This plot presents a global view of the balance between
library complexity and enrichment. There are two arms, one with low
ARC, which corresponds to regions formed by few aligned positions , and
the other where the URCR decreases as the ARC increases.
3B - Min depth vs. FSR - This plot depicts how quickly the distribution of the
FSR approximates the median. In a high quality dataset sample, the median
is around 0.5, and the other quantiles reach that value quickly.
3C - Min depth vs. Proportion of Islands - This plot provides a more detailled
view of the FSR. Islands with low depth then to have reads only from one
strand. Hence, the plot compares the percentage of islands that contain at
